# Copy to .env.local for local dev (required — without Supabase keys the app can show a blank page).
# You can copy VITE_* / REACT_APP_* values from mobile/.env (EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* → VITE_SUPABASE_*).
# In Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview), set ALL of:
#   VITE_BACKEND_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL
# (REACT_APP_* copies optional but recommended during migration.)
# Project Root Directory: frontend (or use repo-root vercel.json).
# Vite uses VITE_* ; REACT_APP_* still works during migration.

# API origin only (no /api/v1 path)
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://trimit-az5h.onrender.com
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://trimit-az5h.onrender.com

# Supabase (same project as mobile/backend)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key
REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key

# Live Vercel site (Play Console privacy/contact URLs)
VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://trimit.online
REACT_APP_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://trimit.online

# Android download (default: Google Drive APK folder). Header + footer use this until Play Store is live.
REACT_APP_DOWNLOAD_APP_URL=https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1jZg_nTVk_tnIh1jPm-rG8ABkeINqrsEW

# Optional — set when app is on Play Console (footer then shows “Google Play” and uses this URL)
# REACT_APP_PLAY_STORE_URL=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.trimit.app

# Backend (Render): PUBLIC_SITE_URL — password-reset email redirect target

# Google Search Console — only if you chose HTML tag verification (not needed for DNS/TXT on Hostinger)
# VITE_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=your_verification_token_here
# REACT_APP_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=your_verification_token_here

# Optional — Google Analytics 4 (separate from Search Console; set if you use GA4)
# REACT_APP_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Optional
REACT_APP_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# ── Google Sign-In (web) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The web app uses Supabase's Google OAuth redirect flow, so NO Google client
# ID/secret is needed in this frontend .env. Configure Google instead in:
#   Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Google
#     • Client ID     = your Google "Web application" OAuth client ID
#     • Client Secret = its secret
#   Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs:
#     • https://trimit.online/auth/callback
#     • http://localhost:3000/auth/callback   (local dev)
#   Google Cloud Console → Credentials → Web client → Authorised redirect URIs:
#     • https://<YOUR_PROJECT>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
# One email = one account: enable Supabase → Auth → "Link identities" (auto-link
# accounts with the same verified email) so Google + OTP never duplicate a user.
